
This is the latest version of xlock (sccs version 23.16) patchlevel = 2.1

CHANGES:
 o now uses Xrm for resource management.
 o locks all screens on a server.
 o new modes: swarm, image and blank.
 o better usage message.
 o support for locking remote machines (X terminals)
 o changed color allocation to non-dynamic (so twm won't complain)
 o center prompt screen (for hires displays).
 o make sure Xlib input buffer does not use up all of swap.
 o make displayed text come from resource file for better I18N.
 o add backward compatible signal handlers for pre 4.1 machines.
 o protect Host access from accessing freed data.
 o autoraise when obscured by a pop-up.
 o searches for machine name aliases.
 o ported to SYSVR4.
 o portable usleep().

